{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>The last two steps of<i>de novo</i>purine biosynthesis are:</p>\n\n<p>i) conversion of 5-aminoimidazole-4-carboxamide-1-beta-D-ribofuranosyl 5'-monophosphate (AICAR) to 5-formaminoimidazole-4-carboxamide-1-beta-D-ribofuranosyl 5'-monophosphate (FAICAR)</p>\n\n<p>ii) conversion of FAICAR to inosine5'-monophopsphate (IMP)</p>\n\n<p>In bacteria and eukaryotes, these steps are catalysed by the well-characterised bifunctional enzyme PurH [[cite:PUB00025174]]. Archaea do not appear to posses PurH, however, and perform these reactions by a different mechanism [[cite:PUB00034499]]. In archaea, step i) is catalysed by the well-conserved PurP protein, while step ii) is catalysed by the PurO enzyme in some (though not all) species [[cite:PUB00034500], [cite:PUB00013793]].</p>\n\n<p>This entry represents the 5-formaminoimidazole-4-carboxamide-1-(beta)-D-ribofuranosyl 5'-monophosphate synthetase also known as PurP.</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure {"accession" "2r85", "name" "Crystal structure of PurP from Pyrococcus furiosus complexed with AMP"}, :overlaps-with nil, :member-databases {"pirsf" {"PIRSF004602" "ATP-grasp protein, PurP type"}, "panther" {"PTHR38147" "5-FORMAMINOIMIDAZOLE-4-CARBOXAMIDE-1-(BETA)-D-RIBOFURANOSYL 5'-MONOPHOSPHATE SYNTHETASE-RELATED"}, "hamap" {"MF_01163" "5-formaminoimidazole-4-carboxamide-1-(beta)-D-ribofuranosyl 5'-monophosphate synthetase [purP]"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "IMP biosynthesis enzyme PurP", "short" "IMP_biosynth_PurP"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 9, "domain_architectures" 0, "proteomes" 131, "taxa" 1443, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 3667, "sets" 0, "proteins" 3665, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 3044}, "pathways" 1}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {"ec" {"displayName" "ENZYME", "description" "ENZYME is a repository of information relati